summary: The first copy I bought of Good Omens back in about 2006 was the Graham Ward cover (1990 Victor Gollancz published). It has...
caption:
The first copy I bought of Good Omens back in about 2006 was the Graham Ward cover (1990 Victor Gollancz published). It has these wonderful chapter heading illustrations - plus those winged hourglasses as cheaper breaks. I love this edition so much (and my copy, with pages glued back in). The caveat is probably one of the best things about it too.

I don’t know if @fuckyeahgoodomens is interested in this (or will even see this) but snake Crowley! He’s the first one to appear in the book.

(It seems other editions do have these which is great! Although not all do but maybe most)

summary: HEY GUESS WHAT So, I quit the Ice Cream Magician job after precisely 5 hours. That’s old news, right?  WELL now I am very extra...
body:
HEY GUESS WHAT

So, I quit the Ice Cream Magician job after precisely 5 hours. That’s old news, right? 

WELL now I am very extra happy that I did, because I now have a job as a cover nursery maid, AND as a libraaaariiaaaaannnn! …. Erm… As well as 8 hours a month as a cleaner, and 15 hours a week as a temporary admin assistant…. And an unspecified number of hours a month as an interviewer for other nursery applicants… 

I … might have too many jobs now.

But

!!!!NURSERY MAID AND LIBRARIAN!!!!

OMG

Does this mean I can now be Crowley (/Nanny Ashtoreth) AND Aziraphale? 

EXCITED

Anyway.

Oh yeah also I found out that a park that I Iove near my new house is on the site of an 11th century castle, and I found some of the ruins, and then realised the whole damn weird-topography of the park is just the moat and ramparts of the castle and then I spent an hour “walking the ramparts” pretending to be a rebel mage in Dragon Age.

When is the bad stuff going to hit? I feel like the universe is lining me up for a crash…

summary: Adam sort of has four dads
title: Adam sort of has four dads
body:
[EDIT: This applies more to the book as I wrote it before the adaptation was out. Some of these things are slightly different in the show.]

Most dad: Mr Young

Points for: 

  • Smokes a fucking pipe
  • Wears 1930s style jumpers
  • Just wants to read his damn newspaper in peace

Points against: 

  • Not many. Sure, he’s not the biological father of the Antichrist, but is still more dad than the devil, so…

2nd place: Aziraphale

Points for: 

  • Does not know what the young’uns are into these days 
  • Dresses like an old ancient man
  • Children (and a few other people) find him very embarrassing

Points against: 

  • Didn’t he suggest killing Adam at one point?
  • Accidentally ended up raising Warlock instead

3rd place: Crowley

Points for: 

  • It was his idea to work with his long-time adversary associate friend to help raise the boy
  • Is enthusiastic about ducks
  • Once bought fuel so he could get James Bond bullet hole stickers for his car

Points against: 

  • Unfortunately, due to that whole mixup at the hospital, he did not actually raise the boy
  • His neat, white Mayfair flat is not child-friendly good lord

Least dad: Literally, Satan

Points for: 

  • Is technically the most dad, biologically speaking
  • Got his son a pet dog (sure, it was a hellhound, but whatever)

Points against: 

  • Did not actually raise his son
  • Wanted Adam to destroy the world (I mean, what kind of example is that setting?)
